fields.description: There are many places to visit in Nepal. Pokhara is one of the most exciting and adventurous place and is also known as piece of a heaven in earth. Pokhara, surrounded by different Himalayan Ranges, commits the visitors with many unbelievable sceneries and adds up the value in their experience by providing different remarkable places.
fields.titles: Places you must visit in Pokhara
fields.title: Places you must visit in Pokhara

fields.description: Pokhara is an amazing and one of the most beautiful city. All the people who visit Nepal can’t resist to visit this city of natural beauty. There are many things to do. And from those there are some of the things that shouldn’t be miss while visiting Pokhara.
fields.title: Things to do in Pokhara

fields.description: Mount Everest (8848ft), highest peak in the world, is also known as Chomolungma in Tibetan language and Sagarmatha in Nepali language. It is located at Solukhumbu district in the range of Mahalangur Himal, the great Himalayas. Sir Edmund Hillary and Tenzing Norgay were the first to scale the mountain in 1953. It has been climbed for more than 5,600 times
fields.title: Mount Everest

fields.description: Chitwan, thrilling destination to feel the wildlife adventure of different kind ­ Jungle Safari,Elephant Bathing, Boating, Chepang Hill , Bird watching and lots more.
fields.title: Chitwan, thrilling destination

fields.description: Nepal is the only country in the modern world that does not have a rectangular national flag, consisting of two united pennant (triangular flag) shapes. It is crimson with blue borders and incorporates stylized symbols of the sun and moon. The blue border on the flag of Nepal signifies peace and harmony, whereas crimson color signifies victory and bravery; the color of rhododendron(the national flower of Nepal). It is said that the national flag of Nepal anticipates that the nation will last as long as the sun and moon is there on earth.
fields.titles: Flag of Nepal ­ Pride of the nation
fields.title: Flag of Nepal ­ Pride of the nation

fields.description: SHERPA, are courageous and dedicated people who first settled in the Solukhumbu District (Khumbu), Nepal ;then they gradually moved westward along salt trade routes. Looking back at the history, Khumbu Sherpa people accomplish autonomy within the newly formed Nepali state. In the 1960s, as tension with China increased, Nepali government influence on the Sherpa people grew.
fields.title: The Bold Sherpas

fields.description: People have always wondered what it feels like to fly like a bird. Paragliding can give you a wonderful flying experience. It is unique, simplest and adventurous sports that offers excitement, relaxation for adventure­seekers.
fields.title: Paragliding in Nepal

What is Simplify tour
What is simplify tour? Simplify Tour is a tourism site which launch packages for tourist. According to the condition, legal state and privacy policy, they can buy these packages. The package is available and on the basis of package, the buyer can visit the different places of Nepal. At the current moment, simplify tour has bought packages only for Nepal.
